member.summary:
Use this method to retrieve the internal buffer as byte[]. Decomcrypts only apply to non-Letter data.
Combine this with AMQP header X-CR-OBJECTTYPE to get message wrapper payloads.
Header Example: ("X-CR-OBJECTTYPE", "LETTER")
Header Example: ("X-CR-OBJECTTYPE", "MESSAGE") Note: Always decomrypts Letter bodies to get type regardless of parameters.

member.name: M:CookedRabbit.Core.Pools.ChannelPool.ReturnChannelAsync(CookedRabbit.Core.Pools.IChannelHost,System.Boolean)
member.summary:
Returns the back to the .
All Aqmp IModel Channels close server side on error, so you have to indicate to the library when that happens.
The library does its best to listen for a dead , but nothing is as reliable as the user flagging the channel for replacement.
Users flag the channel for replacement (e.g. when an error occurs) on it's next use.

member.name: M:CookedRabbit.Core.Pools.ConnectionHost.HealthyAsync
member.summary:
Due to the complexity of the RabbitMQ Dotnet Client there are a few odd scenarios. Just casually check Health() when looping through Connections, skip when not Healthy.
AutoRecovery = False yields results like Closed, Dead, and IsOpen will be true, true, false or false, false, true.
AutoRecovery = True, yields difficult results like Closed, Dead, And IsOpen will be false, false, false or true, true, true (and other variations).
